Option: You can watch these video tutorials:
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xuB1Id2Wxak
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SWYqp7iY_Tc
  Learn Git in 20 Minutes
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y9XZQO1n_7c

Download git from:
  git-scm.com

git default editor setting:
  ~/.linuxbrew/.git/config
  In [core]section, add:
    editor=vim

git Bash:
  mkdir App
  cd App
    git init
    touch index.html app.js
    (then edit the 2 files)

global config:
  git config --global user.name 'losacii'
  git config --global user.email 'me@gmail.com'

Add:
  git add <filename>
  or
    git add .
  or 
    git add *.txt

Commit:
  git commit

git status:
  git status

Ignore files and dirs:
  touch .gitignore log.txt
  then write 'log.txt' into .gitignore first line;

  git add.
  git status

git Brach:
  git branch login
  (go branch login) git checkout login
  touch login.html
  (edit login.html, just simple altering it)
  git add.
  git commit -m 'Added Login'
  (then use 'git checkout **', and 'dir', you will see file system are 
   different)

Merge:
  (git checkout masger)
  git merge login

github.com:
  (New repository ...)
  (you will see some cmdlines:
    git init
    git add README.md
    git commit -m 'Added README'
    git remote add origin https://github.com/losacii/myAppSample.git
    gut push -u grigin master)
    (tpye them in your App dir)

In App dir:
  git remote add origin https://github.com/losacii/myAppSample.git
  git push -u origin master
  (input username and passwd)

Pull or Push:
  Pull:
    git clone <url>
    or
      (go to App dir)
      git pull

Jump the passwd:
  cd /
  git config --global credential.helper store
  cat ~/.gitconfig
  (you will see:
    [user]
        name = losacii
        email = losacii5@gmail.com
    [credential]
        helper = store  )
  git push (again)
  (input passwd, and you won't do it again from now on)

Reset Remote ssh push&pull:
  git remote rm origin
  git remote add origin git@github.com:username/repository.git
  git push -u origin master

  (the you can use
  'git remote -v'
  to see infos)

Add, Commit, Push:
  git add .
  git commit -m '<change log>'
  git push



  
